The #1 all-time recording on the Sacrament of Reconciliation is must-listening for practicing and non-practicing Catholics alike. Riveting, hilarious, insightful, earthy, and inspirational. An essential parish resource for RCIA, Youth Ministry, and Adult Education. You will never experience this most important sacrament in the same way again.

Father Larry Richards is the founder and president of The Reason for Our Hope Foundation. He is a preacher and retreat master who speaks from experience as a pastor of an inner city parish, a high school chaplain, a counselor and evangelist. He hosts a nightly radio show called Changed Forever with Father Larry Richards, heard nationwide on Relevant Radio, and has directed hundreds of retreats, parish missions, and conferences. 

In just a few short years, &quot;Confession&quot; has become one of the most popular and life-changing Catholic recordings of all time. Father Larry Richards has given this talk hundreds of times during his priesthood. Every time, many of his listeners return to the Sacrament of Reconciliation with humility, sincere contrition, and renewed hope for a closer relationship with Jesus Christ. You will no doubt want to give &quot;Confession&quot; to others. Many of the folks you reach (real people in broken relationships with Our Lord) will return to Confession and find healing.

Based on a proven and powerful parish mission presentation, &quot;Confession&quot; has become the #1 talk in North America on this most misunderstood sacrament because it is humorous (even hilarious), riveting, honest, human, and often touchingly gentle. It confronts without being confrontational. It persuades without being manipulative.

This talk has helped countless listeners comprehend what sin really is, sometimes for the first time since we were children. It is just as important for practicing Catholics (even those who go to Confession fairly often) to hear this talk as it is for fallen-away Catholics to hear it.

Give it to your friends. Bring it to your parish. Guide souls towards healing in Christ in one of most glorious, rejuvenating, and intimate ways imaginable.

